COVID-19 Status

As of 5:43PM PT yesterday, over 1.9 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 22.1 thousand have died.

In the last day, 2 thousand new infections were reported and 58 deaths. Currently 2,931 are in the hospital and 77 are in the ICU. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 10.4 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, -18.3% have their 1st shot and 29.1% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 25 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~35 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.
